The paper proposes a method for protein structure determination using convex optimization and statistical tools. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves modeling the protein backbone as an articulated structure composed of rigid units, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and statistical analysis, which suggests that it may belong to the optimization (cs.DS) or computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of experimental data, which suggests that it may also belong to the scientific computing (cs.SI) sub-category.
